div.p:
1 By Apostasie [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] for the worde is meant a departing or going away from that which we formerly stood to, and followed: for the matter, we vnderstand hereby in short, the forsaking of true religion in the doctrine of it, or in the practise: for it must be noted that men become backsliders from religion two waies.
